            <thetext>The FocusHandler does support stepping through (=focusing) the different widgets by hitting the &quot;TAB&quot; key. This stepping should only be possible with widgets that are childs of the current focus root.

So if a window widget (which itself is an own focus root) is present and the user steps through the widgets of the application the widgets inside the window widget should *not* be focused.</thetext>
